05:30 AM. You wake up feeling groggy. The alarm buzzes insistently. You groan and sit up, rubbing your eyes.
You mumble: &ldquo;Wolly, anything important happen overnight?&rdquo;
A soft glow pulses above your phone, and Wolly materializes — your AI assistant, slightly pixelated this early.
Wolly: &ldquo;Plenty happened. But maybe start with a coffee first.&rdquo;
You shuffle to the kitchen, start the machine, and lean against the counter as the coffee brews.

Why I Disagree with the Saying: &ldquo;If You&rsquo;re Not Interested in Politics, Politics Will Still Affect You&rdquo;
I don’t like this saying, and here’s why:
It&rsquo;s False. Lets reverse the logic. What happens if you are interested in Politics. It affects you. What happens if you are not interested in Politics? It affects you. So no matter what you do the Politics affects you. The statements create illusion that your interest makes a difference Interest in Politics is Not a Necessity.
